---
/* Homepage composition for the one-page Dresden Systems Meetup website. */

import InfoCard from "../components/InfoCard.astro";
import PastMeetups from "../components/PastMeetups.astro";
import { pastMeetups } from "../data/meetups";
import { nextMeetup } from "../data/next-meetup";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const description =
  "The regular Systems Meetup in Dresden for everyone in Low-Level space (virtualization, x86, arm, device drivers, operating systems, research, ...).";
---

<BaseLayout title="Dresden Systems Meetup" description={description}>
  <main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 py-6 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header
      class="mb-6 border-b border-slate-200 pb-4 sm:flex sm:items-end sm:justify-between sm:gap-8"
    >
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-950">
        Dresden Systems Meetup
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600 sm:mt-0 sm:max-w-xl sm:text-right">
        Also known as <em>Mikrokernstammtisch</em> or
        <em><abbr title="Microkernel Valley">ukvly</abbr></em> meetup from before
        2019.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section
      class="mb-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 p-6 text-blue-950 shadow-sm shadow-blue-100/70"
      role="region"
      aria-labelledby="next-meetup-heading"
    >
      <h2
        id="next-meetup-heading"
        class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl"
      >
        Next Meetup
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg font-medium">
        📅 {nextMeetup.date} ⏰ {nextMeetup.time} 📍 {nextMeetup.location}
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-blue-900">
        <small>{nextMeetup.registrationNote}</small><br />
        {nextMeetup.hostNote}
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="About & Topics">
          <p>
            A regular meetup for all people in Dresden and the surrounding area
            working in systems context. This includes but is not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>ARM, RISC-V, x86</li>
            <li>Academia and Research</li>
            <li>Device Drivers</li>
            <li>Firmware</li>
            <li>Operating Systems</li>
            <li>Virtualization</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We usually get around 25-40 attendees. If the interest goes beyond
            what the venue can handle, we may have to close registration.
          </p>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Core Values">
          <ul>
            <li>Friendly and open-minded environment</li>
            <li>"Du"-Anrede highly encouraged</li>
            <li>
              We always switch to English, if non-native speakers prefer so
            </li>
            <li>
              Keep it simple. No big processes. Meet, talk, and
              <strong>have fun</strong>!
            </li>
            <li>
              <a
                href="https://berlincodeofconduct.org"
                title="Our code of conduct"
              >
                Our Code of Conduct
              </a>
              <small>(the state from 2024-05-24 is the reference)</small>
            </li>
            <li>
              Everyone interested in the field is welcome. This includes
              students and people with little knowledge and experience so far.
            </li>
            <li>Event for people, not for companies</li>
          </ul>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Past Meetups">
          <PastMeetups meetups={pastMeetups} />
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Organization">
          <ul>
            <li>
              We have one main organizer and an event host that changes from
              event to event. Currently, Philipp Schuster takes care of the
              general coordination, whereas the changing event host provides a
              room and prepares a setup to give presentations etc.
            </li>
            <li>
              Just message Philipp or talk to him at a meetup, to host an event!
            </li>
            <li>
              Lightning talks, tech talks, and demos are highly appreciated. The
              ability to give talks however depends on the location. We inform
              you in the announcements and ask for talks / inform for
              limitations.
            </li>
            <li>
              Each meeting starts with 30-60 minutes of talks / demos, followed
              by an open evening.
            </li>
            <li>
              Paid drinks and food are not guaranteed but likely! We will update
              the next meetup info accordingly. Typically, we have pizza 🍕 and
              drinks 🍻. In case you have a location and want to host, but have
              no funding, we have companies in our community who might be happy
              to sponsor your event. Feel free to reach out!
              <small
                >Hint: Pizza and drinks for 30 people cost ~300-400 Euro.</small
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Known Participants">
          <p>Usually we have attendees of people working at:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Amazon (AWS)</li>
            <li>Barkhausen Institut (BI)</li>
            <li>Cyberus Technology</li>
            <li>Genode Labs</li>
            <li>Kernkonzept</li>
            <li>Huawei</li>
            <li>
              TU Dresden
              <small>
                (especially the Operating Systems Chair of Prof. Horst
                Schirmeier)
              </small>
            </li>
            <li>and many more ...</li>
          </ul>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Announcement and Discussion Channels">
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Matrix </strong> Space with channels for announcements and discussions:<br
              />
              <a
                title="Matrix space with all channels"
                href="https://matrix.to/#/#dd-systems-meetup:cyberus-technology.de"
              >
                <code>#dd-systems-meetup:cyberus-technology.de</code>
              </a>
              <br /><small
                >Use this if your Matrix client supports spaces! Otherwise:</small
              >
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <small>
                    <a
                      title="Matrix announcements channel"
                      href="https://matrix.to/#/#dd-systems-meetup-announcements:cyberus-technology.de"
                    >
                      Announcements channel only
                    </a>
                  </small>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <small>
                    <a
                      title="Matrix discussion channel"
                      href="https://matrix.to/#/#dd-systems-meetup-discussions:cyberus-technology.de"
                    >
                      Discussion channel only
                    </a>
                  </small>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Email List</strong>
              <br />
              <small>
                We have a mailing list at
                <code>sysmeetup@os.inf.tu-dresden.de</code>
                maintained by TU Dresden, with a few selected trusted moderators from
                the community. You can subscribe using the
                <a
                  href="https://os.inf.tu-dresden.de/mailman3/postorius/lists/sysmeetup.os.inf.tu-dresden.de"
                  title="Mailing List Sign-Up"
                >
                  online form
                </a>
                . Usually 2-4 emails per quarter.
                <br />
                Due to spammers auto-subscribing (really...), please <b>also</b>
                send a short mail from the account you are subscribing with to the
                list admins reachable at the address shown on the online form. Some
                nice words are appreciated :)
              </small>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mastodon</strong>:
              <a
                href="https://mastodon.social/@dd_systems_meetup"
                title="Announcements on Mastodon"
              >
                <code>@dd_systems_meetup@mastodon.social</code>
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="line-through">X</span>
              <strong>Twitter</strong>:
              <a
                href="https://twitter.com/ukvly"
                title="Announcements on Twitter / X"
              >
                <code>@ukvly</code>
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>This website</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <small>
              For discussions, I'm kindly asking you to use the provided Matrix
              channel rather than email, if possible. I'm nevertheless happy to
              respond to emails as well.
            </small>
          </p>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="When and Where">
          <p>
            Every 2-4 months with 3-5 meetups per year, usually on a Thursday
            18:00 to 22:00 o'clock. The location changes. Feel free to reach out
            and host a meetup!
          </p>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
      <div>
        <InfoCard title="Trivia">
          <p>
            Dresden has a rich ecosystem of companies and research in the field
            of operating systems and systems engineering in general. Especially,
            between ~2000 and ~2017, there was a "golden era" of microkernels,
            both in academia and various local companies. That's where the term
            <em>ukvly</em> (microkernel valley) originates from.
          </p>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer
      class="mt-8 border-t border-slate-200 pt-4 text-sm text-slate-500 [&_a]:font-medium [&_a]:text-blue-700 hover:[&_a]:text-blue-900 hover:[&_a]:underline"
    >
      {new Date().getFullYear()}
      - The systems community of Dresden • Website operated by
      <a href="https://phip1611.de" title="Philipp Schuster">Philipp Schuster</a
      >
      • Source on
      <a
        href="https://github.com/phip1611/dd-systems-meetup-website"
        title="GitHub"
      >
        GitHub
      </a>
    </footer>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
